cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with image representation and uses a neural network approach, which suggests it falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus on illumination invariance and the use of specialized loss functions also suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of the BigTime dataset and analysis of patch matching and rigid registration suggest a neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of generating representations that are invariant to general types of nuisance suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
